The following may be paticularly relevant to stock price movements in this context.

  1. EaringsPerShare:
  2. ForecastEarningsPerShare:
  3. DisclosedDate:
  • If the expected earings per share is higher than the previous period, the stock price may rise in the future. Unfortunately, there seems to be a lot of NA.
  • Price movements are expected to be large on the disclosure date.

The stock market closes at 3:00 p.m. We believe that earnings disclosure after 3:00 p.m. has a greater impact on price movements the next day than on that day. For this reason, I will move the disclosure date by one day for earnings discoosures after 3:00 p.m.

financials %>% 
  mutate(
    DisclosedDate = if_else(
      DisclosedTime>=as.ITime("15:00:00"), DisclosedDate + 1, DisclosedDate
      )
    )
